        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 10:57AM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 1057 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Red Mesa, or 31 miles east of Mexican Hat, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aneth and Montezuma Creek.

This includes Utah 162 between mile markers 6 and 25.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
